# REFERENCE ONLY — env var NAMES, no values, safe in a public repo.
#
# There is NO secret file in this repo (it is open source). Secrets live ONLY
# in the gated `prod` GitHub Environment. `standup.yml` maps each Environment
# secret to one of these ARXII_* env vars ON THE ansible-playbook STEP ONLY;
# the secrets_vault role reads them via lookup('env', ...) and renders the
# 0600 on-box EnvironmentFile. Local-fallback: the operator exports the same
# ARXII_* vars from a password manager (never on the command line).
#
# ON-BOX set (decision 10) — required:
#   ARXII_PG_PASSWORD
#   ARXII_DJANGO_SECRET_KEY
#   ARXII_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME, ARXII_CLOUDINARY_API_KEY,
#     ARXII_CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET   (three discrete secrets, not one
#                                    CLOUDINARY_URL — settings.py's
#                                    cloudinary.config() reads each
#                                    individually via env(), each with an
#                                    explicit default="" kwarg, so a single
#                                    combined URL var would be silently
#                                    ignored rather than erroring)
#   ARXII_RESEND_API_KEY
#   ARXII_BACKUP_WRITER_ACCESS_KEY
#   ARXII_BACKUP_WRITER_SECRET_KEY
#   ARXII_R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID
#   ARXII_R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
#   ARXII_OFFBOX_ALERT_TOKEN
#   ARXII_CADDY_CF_DNS_TOKEN   (Cloudflare DNS-edit-scoped token for Caddy
#                               ACME DNS-01 — distinct from the provisioning
#                               Cloudflare token; bucket... zone-scoped)
#   ARXII_DJANGO_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD  (first-run Django superuser password;
#                                     consumed once by `evennia
#                                     createsuperuser --noinput`, then
#                                     long-lived for any future re-create
#                                     after a superuser deletion)
#
# Non-secret companions (set as gated Environment VARIABLES, not Secrets;
# default to `arxii_admin` / `admin@example.invalid` if unset):
#   ARXII_DJANGO_SUPERUSER_USERNAME
#   ARXII_DJANGO_SUPERUSER_EMAIL
#
# ON-BOX set (decision 10) — OPTIONAL (#2236 Phase 5): missing/empty just
# disables the feature, never refuses the converge (secrets_vault's
# secrets_map_optional, not secrets_map; standup.sh's REQUIRED_ARXII does
# NOT include it):
#   ARXII_SENTRY_DSN  (Sentry error/performance monitoring DSN; settings.py
#                      only calls sentry_sdk.init() when this is non-empty)
#
# Non-secret, PROVISIONING/ORCHESTRATION-side (read by standup.sh itself /
# fed to Terraform; never reach the box, never touch the ansible step's env):
#   ARXII_SSH_ADMIN_CIDRS  (required) — JSON list of operator CIDRs, e.g.
#                           '["203.0.113.10/32"]'; maps to TF_VAR_ssh_admin_
#                           cidrs. standup.sh's preflight refuses to run if
#                           unset — a conscious decision, not a silent open
#                           default (see README "DECISION — SSH admin
#                           source CIDR allowlist").
#   ARXII_ACME_EMAIL       (optional) — Caddy's ACME account email; defaults
#                           to admin@<TF_VAR_domain> if unset.
#
# MUST NOT be present in the ansible-playbook step's env (operator/CI-only;
# they belong to the tofu step, never on the box):
#   ARXII_LINODE_TOKEN, ARXII_CLOUDFLARE_TOKEN
#
# NOT an ARXII_* var at all — DERIVED on-box, not operator-supplied: the
# secrets_vault EnvironmentFile also renders DATABASE_URL (from
# ARXII_PG_PASSWORD, urlencode-filtered) and FRONTEND_URL/SITE_URL (from the
# dh_web_fqdn group_var, itself from the tofu web_fqdn output). settings.py
# reads all three via env() at its normal (non-overlay) import time — see
# roles/secrets_vault/templates/arxii.env.j2 for the exact computation.
#
# #2236 Phase 3 P1 (dress rehearsal, gated `stage` Environment, NOT `prod`):
# rehearse.sh generates ARXII_PG_PASSWORD/ARXII_DJANGO_SECRET_KEY/
# ARXII_DJANGO_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD itself (openssl rand — never operator-
# supplied) and leaves ARXII_RESEND_API_KEY, the Cloudinary trio, the R2
# pair, ARXII_OFFBOX_ALERT_TOKEN, and ARXII_CADDY_CF_DNS_TOKEN unset
# (rehearsal_mode + vault_allow_empty — see roles/secrets_vault/defaults/
# main.yml). It reuses ARXII_AUTHORIZED_KEYS from the same var name/value as
# prod. See infra/README.md's "Dress rehearsal" section for the full stage
# Environment secret contract (STAGE_LINODE_TOKEN, STAGE_TF_STATE_*, etc.) —
# a separate, smaller set than this file's prod contract above.
